  "market_context": "Hourly chart showed a reversal candle (Tuesday) with aggressive lower open followed by strong recovery close near open, establishing bearish bias. Analyst shifted to 5-minute for entry on Wednesday continuation.",
  "key_observation": "On the 5-minute chart, price reached a fair value gap, then closed below an up-close candle—confirming change in state of delivery and enabling a bearish continuation entry.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Identified a bearish reversal candle on the hourly chart (Tuesday), forming a swing point with aggressive lower open and strong recovery close near open.",
    "Step 2: Shifted analysis to the 5-minute timeframe to seek continuation entries aligned with the hourly bearish bias.",
    "Step 3: Marked a fair value gap (FVG) on the 5-minute chart as a point of interest where price was expected to react.",
    "Step 4: Observed price reaching into the FVG and closing below the prior up-close candle, confirming a change in state of delivery (CISD).",
    "Step 5: Took a short entry on the open of the next candle, using the protected swing as stop placement and targeting sell-side liquidity via standard deviation projections (-1, -2, -2.5, -4, -4.5)."
  ],
  "outcome": "Price moved lower and took out the lows; trade achieved target (2R or beyond) as confirmed by analyst statement 'we do get there'.",
  "lessons": "Focus on reversal candles (Candle 2 closures) that form clean swings with CISD confirmation; avoid trading expansion-heavy Candle 2s. Continuations after valid reversals offer higher-probability setups.",
